@shruti0103 looking like a dream on her wedding day .
It was her trust in me that led to this look . She always likes her hair side parted but for this look I insisted on changing to a centre part and she agreed , she didn’t want to wear a Nath so i suggested a diamanté bindi and she agreed . Every bit of beauty that she holds inside of her was reflecting on her face this day . I don’t know how to even put this look into words , but all I can say is that she just looked mesmerising

latestPosts.caption:
Honoured to be awarded the Best Bridal makeup artist second time in a row . Out of 136k businesses listed with wedmegood only 370 were chosen to be winners in different fields catering to the wedding industry , and winning this second time in a row only is a testament that hard work pays off.

With a heart full of gratitude I would like to thank all the people who trusted us for curating their looks for their events . Me along with my team are humbled by your love and affection. With each award we strive harder to create the most stunning looks for our clients . 

A huge thank you to @wedmegood @mehaksagar_wmg for organising the event and recognising the hard work of each of the winners .

 Thank you @mysecretnest for being with me on such a special day , aise hi nahi bolte friends make special days even more special .

Thank you @vogueshaire for capturing these moments

HAVE YOU EVER DONE THIS 
Here’s why I did what I did
Here’s a technique that not many artists talk about but works like a charm on small eyes. 

My client had smaller eyes and very minimal lid space so I decided to do individual lashes and carefully placed them under her lash line . This needs a lot of skill and precision so one needs to do it very carefully . This ensured that the lashes weren’t taking up any lid space so the eyes could look more open and the lashes added the needed depth which enhanced the definition of the lash line .
Hope you found this helpful .
